---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---
<Layout title="Work with Wendy Ting" description="Work with Wendy Ting — integrative oncology naturopath offering personalised cancer support alongside your existing care.">
  <Nav />

  <main>
    <section class="practitioner">
      <div class="container">

        <!-- Practitioner header -->
        <div class="practitioner-grid">
          <div>
            <div class="eyebrow">Wendy Ting</div>
            <h1>An integrative approach to cancer care</h1>
            <p>Supporting you through your cancer journey with clarity, care, and a personalised approach that meets you where you are—so you can move forward with greater steadiness and understanding.</p>
            <div class="cta-row">
              <a class="btn primary" href="/booking">Book a consultation</a>
            </div>
          </div>
<img src="/public/Wendy short hair.jpg"/>
          <div class="qualifications-card card" style="min-height: 360px; justify-content:center;">
            <h3>Qualifications &amp; Training</h3>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>Bachelor of Natural Medicine (Degree-qualified Naturopath)</li>
              <li>Certified Terrain Advocate, Metabolic Terrain Institute of Health (USA)</li>
              <li>Certified Radical Remission Coach &amp; Workshop Instructor (USA)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        <!-- Story blocks -->
        <div class="stack-grid">

          <div class="story-block">
            <h3>Just diagnosed? Start here</h3>
            <p>Being told you have cancer can feel like the most devastating news — and, for some, the beginning of seeing life with a different kind of clarity.</p>
            <p>When everything feels urgent and uncertain, the first step is not to do everything — it's to understand what matters most, and to move forward with a clear, considered plan.</p>
            <p><strong>Here's how you can be supported right from the start:</strong></p>
            <ul class="clean">
              <li>Make sense of your diagnosis, reports, and treatment options</li>
              <li>Understand what is standard of care — and where you may have choices</li>
              <li>Identify what matters now (and what can wait)</li>
              <li>Review supplements, herbs, and diet for safety alongside treatment</li>
              <li>Reduce overwhelm and conflicting advice</li>
              <li>Support your body through treatment (energy, side effects, nutrition)</li>
              <li>Map out a clear, structured roadmap for the next phase</li>
            </ul>
            <p>You don't need to have everything figured out. You need clarity, structure, and the right guidance — and that's what we build together.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="story-block">
            <p>You may also be wondering if there is more you can do — beyond simply following treatment.</p>
            <p>Wendy's work is grounded in integrative oncology and metabolic approaches, informed by Radical Remission research and the Metabolic Terrain Institute of Health (USA). Radical Remission explores cases where individuals with very poor or terminal prognoses went on to fully recover, seeking to understand the patterns and factors that may support the body's healing process. Alongside this, a metabolic approach considers cancer within the context of the body's internal environment — including energy production, inflammation, and the broader terrain that may influence outcomes.</p>
            <p>Together, these perspectives offer a more considered, whole-person framework — one that supports you alongside your medical treatment, not in place of it.</p>
            <p>In practice, this means working step by step to bring clarity to your situation — using functional and blood testing where appropriate, and integrating nutrition, practitioner-grade supplementation, and supportive therapies in a way that is measured, strategic, and aligned with your stage of care.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="story-block">
            <h3>Wendy has lived this journey herself.</h3>
            <p>Diagnosed with Stage IV metastatic breast cancer and given an initial prognosis of 3 months, she faced the same fear and uncertainty that you may be experiencing now. What followed was not just survival, but a profound shift in perspective. While the diagnosis was initially devastating, it became a powerful turning point — a wake-up call that brought clarity to what truly matters and a deeper understanding of what it means to heal.</p>
            <p>Rather than being defined by the diagnosis, she chose to understand it — to learn, to question, and to engage actively in her own care. This perspective continues to shape how she supports others: with clarity, steadiness, and a deep respect for the complexity of each individual journey.</p>
            <p>Now, as a degree-qualified naturopath and medical herbalist, she brings together lived experience and clinical training to guide others through this process — offering support that is clear, grounded, and deeply practical, especially in moments where steadiness and direction matter most.</p>
          </div>

        </div>

      </div>
    </section>
</style>
	<head>
		<meta charset="utf-8" />
		<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="/favicon.svg" />
		<link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
		<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width" />
		<meta name="generator" content={Astro.generator} />
		<title>Astro</title>
	</head>
	<body>
		<h1>Astro</h1>
	</body>
</html>

    <!-- CTA Band -->
    <section class="cta-band">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>You don't have to navigate this alone.</h2>
        <p>Book a consultation with Wendy to begin your integrative oncology journey.</p>
        <div class="cta-row" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/booking">Book a consultation</a>
          <a class="btn secondary" href="/contact">Get in touch first</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
